<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>JavaScript Number Methods PJH</h2>

<p>The isInteger() method returns true if the argument is an integer.</p>
<p>Otherwise it returns false.</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
Number.isInteger(10) + "<br>" + Number.isInteger(10.5);
</script>

</body>
</html>


*


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>JavaScript Number Methods PJH</h2>

<p>The isFinite() method returns false if the argument is Infinity or NaN.</p>
<p>Otherwise it returns true.</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
isFinite(10 / 0) + "<br>" + isFinite(10 / 1);
</script>

</body>
</html>


*


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>JavaScript Arrow Functions PJH</h2>

<p>Arrow functions are not supported in IE11 or earlier.</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
const x = (x, y) => { return x * y };
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = x(5, 5);
</script>

</body>
</html>